2 MCMC

# pledger data:
s1 <- 424
s2 <- 5416
n1 <- 777
n2 <- 9072

data  <- list("s1","s2","n1","n2") # to be passed on to JAGS

myinits <- list(
  list(theta1 = runif(1), theta2 = runif(1), theta1prior = runif(1), theta2prior = runif(1)),
  list(theta1 = runif(1), theta2 = runif(1), theta1prior = runif(1), theta2prior = runif(1)),
  list(theta1 = runif(1), theta2 = runif(1), theta1prior = runif(1), theta2prior = runif(1)))

parameters <- c("theta1", "theta2", "delta", "deltaprior")

model_text <- "
# Pledgers
model{
  # Rates and Difference
  theta1 ~ dbeta(1,1)
  theta2 ~ dbeta(1,1)
  delta <- theta1-theta2  
  
  # Data
  s1 ~ dbin(theta1,n1)
  s2 ~ dbin(theta2,n2)
  
  # Prior Sampling
  theta1prior ~ dbeta(1,1)
  theta2prior ~ dbeta(1,1)
  deltaprior <- theta1prior-theta2prior
}
"

samples <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                 model.file = textConnection(model_text),
                 n.chains=3, n.iter=10000,
         n.burnin=1000, n.thin=1, DIC=T)

# Collect posterior samples across all chains:
delta.posterior  <- samples$BUGSoutput$sims.list$delta      
delta.prior      <- samples$BUGSoutput$sims.list$deltaprior

logspline 피팅으로 계산한 BF. bound 설정 여부는 큰 영향이 없다.

library(polspline)
fit.prior     <- logspline(delta.prior, lbound=-1, ubound=1)  # 여기에서는 bound 영향 거의 없다.
fit.posterior <- logspline(delta.posterior, lbound=-1, ubound=1)

# 95% confidence interval:
# ( x0 <- qlogspline(0.025,fit.posterior) )
# ( x1 <- qlogspline(0.975,fit.posterior) )
qlogspline(c(0.025, 0.975), fit.posterior)
[1] -0.08739238 -0.01525240

95% CI는 영점을 포함하지 않았다. 그러나,

posterior <- dlogspline(0, fit.posterior) # this gives the pdf at point delta = 0
prior <- dlogspline(0, fit.prior)     # based on the logspline fit
( BF01 <- posterior/prior )
[1] 0.4938913
( BF01 <- posterior ) # because we know the height of the prior equals 1 at delta = 0
[1] 0.4679124

\(BF01\) = 0.47이고 \(BF10\) = 2.14에 불과하였다.

\(\delta\)는 \(\theta_1 \sim uniform(0,1)\)과 \(\theta_2 \sim uniform(0,1)\)의 차이이므로 높이가 1인 삼각 분포(triangular distribution)이다. 즉, 영점밀도가 1이다. 따라서 prior의 영점밀도를 추정하지 않고 1을 사용해도 된다.

( BF01 <- posterior ) # because we know the height of the prior equals 1 at delta = 0
[1] 0.4679124

6 Exercise 9.1.4

Test for equality of proportions에서 두 집단의 차이는 유의미하다.

prop.test(c(s1,s2), c(n1,n2), alternative = c("two.sided")) #approximate

    2-sample test for equality of proportions with continuity correction

data:  c(s1, s2) out of c(n1, n2)
X-squared = 7.5966, df = 1, p-value = 0.005848
alternative hypothesis: two.sided
95 percent confidence interval:
 -0.08844734 -0.01417909
sample estimates:
   prop 1    prop 2 
0.5456885 0.5970018

여기를 참고하여, 두 표본의 크기가 다를 때의 효과크기를 계산하였다.

library(pwr)
p1 <- s1/n1
p2 <- s2/n2
h <-abs(2*asin(sqrt(p1))-2*asin(sqrt(p2))); 
h # Non-directional h, magnitude of difference
[1] 0.1037368
# directional h, pwr.2p2n.test works either directional or non-directional h anyway
h2 <- ES.h(p1, p2)
h2
[1] -0.1037368
pwr.2p2n.test(h, n1=n1, n2=n2, sig.level=0.05)

     difference of proportion power calculation for binomial distribution (arcsine transformation) 

              h = 0.1037368
             n1 = 777
             n2 = 9072
      sig.level = 0.05
          power = 0.7925411
    alternative = two.sided

NOTE: different sample sizes

Cohen의 기준에 따르면, 위 효과크기는 매우 작다고 판단할 수 있다.

  • h = 0.20: “small effect size”.
  • h = 0.50: “medium effect size”.
  • h = 0.80: “large effect size”.
